"{\"uid\": \"myjoyonline.com-paris-olympics-70-teams-qualify-for-relay-events\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Audio By Carbonatix A total of 70 teams have qualified for relay events at the Paris 2024 Olympic Games following two days of thrilling action at the World Athletics Relays Bahamas 24 (4-5 May) Fourteen teams in each of the five disciplines being contested in Nassau - the women's and men's 4x100m and 4x400m plus the mixed 4x400m - automatically qualified for Paris places.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 376, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 151, \"end\": 166, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9716959707764592, \"rank\": 0.029128482647664752, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 262, \"end\": 268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"score\": 0.9715932899889541, \"rank\": 0.028851898299108496, \"text\": \"Nassau\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\"}, {\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999995469023478, \"rank\": 4.5309793302771594e-07, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Audio\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 5}, {\"ngram\": \"Carbonatix A total\", \"from\": 9, \"to\": 27}, {\"ngram\": \"70 teams\", \"from\": 31, \"to\": 39}, {\"ngram\": \"relay events\", \"from\": 59, \"to\": 71}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 75, \"to\": 103}, {\"ngram\": \"two days\", \"from\": 114, \"to\": 122}, {\"ngram\": \"action\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 142}, {\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 189, \"to\": 192}, {\"ngram\": \"Fourteen teams\", \"from\": 194, \"to\": 208}, {\"ngram\": \"the five disciplines\", \"from\": 220, \"to\": 240}, {\"ngram\": \"the women\", \"from\": 269, \"to\": 278}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 288}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first 40 qualified teams were confirmed on Saturday and the final 30 on Sunday, following a second Olympic qualifying round for teams that missed out on day one.\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 542, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first 40 qualified teams\", \"from\": 377, \"to\": 405}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 459}, {\"ngram\": \"a second Olympic qualifying round\", \"from\": 471, \"to\": 504}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 514}, {\"ngram\": \"day\", \"from\": 534, \"to\": 537}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Teams that qualified on Saturday also secured their spots for the respective World Relays finals on Sunday, when they raced for prize money and Olympic lane seeding positions.\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 719, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Teams\", \"from\": 544, \"to\": 549}, {\"ngram\": \"Saturday\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 576}, {\"ngram\": \"their spots\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 601}, {\"ngram\": \"the respective World Relays finals\", \"from\": 606, \"to\": 640}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 644, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 672, \"to\": 683}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic lane seeding positions\", \"from\": 688, \"to\": 718}]}, {\"sentence\": \"USA won four of the five finals in Nassau, the nation's 4x100m women setting a championship record with their 41.85 run and the mixed 4x400m squad achieving the same with their 3:10.73 performance.\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 756, \"end\": 762, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Duchy_of_Nassau\", \"score\": 0.9715932899889541, \"rank\": 0.028851898299108496, \"text\": \"Nassau\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"